<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="101" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="101">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="101">
The transfer of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Triteleia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triteleia japonica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonica">Triteleia japonica</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Leptoteleia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptoteleia renders" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="renders">Leptoteleia renders</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Leptoteleia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptoteleia japonica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonica">Leptoteleia japonica</taxonomicName>
Yamagishi as a junior objective homonym. We hereby provide a replacement name in the interest of nomenclatural clarity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="101" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="101">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="101">
The Latin adjectival epithet 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“striola,”">&quot;striola,&quot;</normalizedToken>
meaning 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“furrow”">&quot;furrow&quot;</normalizedToken>
or 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“line”">&quot;line&quot;</normalizedToken>
, refers to the longitudinal costae mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yamagishi, K" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Entomology" pageId="9" pageNumber="108" pagination="811 - 815" title="A new Japanese species of Leptoteleia Kieffer (Hymenoptera, Scelionidae), reared from eggs of the green tree cricket." volume="61" year="1993">Yamagishi (1993)</bibRefCitation>
as a character useful for the diagnosis for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
